sentences.en: Eggs that are scrambled and eaten with toast are typically unfertilized.
sentences.cn: 我们吃的炒鸡蛋一般来说是未受精的鸡蛋.

sentences.en: Haplodiploid - A reproductive system in which females are diploid and males result from unfertilized, haploid eggs.
sentences.cn: Haplodiploid - 以生殖系统,其中女性和男性二倍体结果未受精, 单倍体卵子.

sentences.en: Sperm race towards the unfertilized egg.
sentences.cn: 精虫朝未受精的卵子冲去.

sentences.en: The unfertilized eggs of a female lobster, which turn a reddish color when cooked.
sentences.cn: 未受精的龙虾卵; 烹饪时变红;用作装饰或给酱油加色.

trans.tran_en: (of an animal, plant, or egg cell) not fertilized
